# Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) Cluster Upgrade Guide (2026)

A complete, production-ready guide for upgrading a **Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) Standard Cluster** using the latest Google Cloud CLI commands.

> **Environment**
>
> - Kubernetes: GKE Standard Cluster
> - Cloud SDK: Latest
> - Upgrade Method: CLI (gcloud)
> - Cluster Name: `lottery-cluster`
> - Zone: `us-central1-a`

---

# Upgrade Flow

```text
                    Check Cluster Health
                             │
                             ▼
                  Check Current Version
                             │
                             ▼
              Check Available GKE Versions
                             │
                             ▼
                Upgrade Control Plane
                             │
                             ▼
             Verify Control Plane Version
                             │
                             ▼
                 Upgrade Node Pool(s)
                             │
                             ▼
                 Verify Node Versions
                             │
                             ▼
              Validate Applications & Pods
                             │
                             ▼
                 Monitor Production
```

---

# Step 1 - Verify Cluster Health

Always verify the cluster before upgrading.

## Check Nodes

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

Expected

```text
NAME                                         STATUS   ROLES    AGE   VERSION
gke-lottery-cluster-default-pool-xxxxx       Ready    <none>   2d    v1.34.x
```

---

## Check Pods

```bash
kubectl get pods -A
```

Ensure

- No CrashLoopBackOff
- No Pending Pods
- All workloads are healthy

---

## Check Deployments

```bash
kubectl get deployment -A
```

---

## Check Services

```bash
kubectl get svc -A
```

---

# Step 2 - Check Current Cluster Version

```bash
gcloud container clusters describe lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a \
    --format="value(currentMasterVersion,currentNodeVersion)"
```

Example

```text
1.34.6-gke.1056000
1.34.6-gke.1056000
```

---

# Step 3 - Check Current Node Pools

```bash
gcloud container node-pools list \
    --cluster lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a
```

Example

```text
NAME            MACHINE_TYPE   VERSION
default-pool    e2-small       1.34.6-gke.1056000
```

---

# Step 4 - Check Available Upgrade Versions

```bash
gcloud container get-server-config \
    --zone us-central1-a
```

Example

```text
Valid Master Versions

1.35.5-gke.1324000
1.35.4-gke.1200000
1.34.9-gke.1000000
```

Choose the version you want.

---

# Step 5 - Upgrade Control Plane

Upgrade only the Kubernetes Control Plane.

```bash
gcloud container clusters upgrade lottery-cluster \
    --master \
    --cluster-version=1.35.5-gke.1324000 \
    --zone us-central1-a
```

Google will ask

```text
Do you want to continue (Y/n)?
```

Type

```
Y
```

---

# Step 6 - Verify Control Plane Version

```bash
gcloud container clusters describe lottery-cluster \
    --zone us-central1-a \
    --format="value(currentMasterVersion)"
```

---

# Step 7 - Upgrade Node Pool

> **Latest CLI Note:** The older `gcloud container node-pools upgrade` command is no longer used. Upgrade node pools using `gcloud container clusters upgrade --node-pool`. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

```bash
gcloud container clusters upgrade lottery-cluster \
    --node-pool=default-pool \
    --cluster-version=1.35.5-gke.1324000 \
    --zone us-central1-a
```

If you omit `--cluster-version`, GKE upgrades the node pool to match the current control plane version. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

